The Law Society of Kenya on Friday expressed confidence justice will be served for the murder of human rights lawyer Willie Kimani, his client and taxi driver.Lawyers marched from the Milimani law courts to the Office of the President through the IG&rsquo;s office.LSK president Isaac Okero said lawyers are satisfied with progress of the trial. He called for speedy prosecution of extrajudicial killings.The LSK unveiled a scroll at the Supreme Court&rsquo;s Museum in commemoration of the fallen heroes.AP officers Fredrick Leliman, Leonard Maina, Stephen Chebulet, Silvia Wanjiku and informer Peter Ngugi are on trial at the Milimani law courts.Kimani, client Josephat Mwenda and driver Joseph Muiruri were abducted on June 23, 2016.This followed a case at the Mavoko courts where Mwenda had accused Leliman of assault. They were brutally killed, their bodies found a week later in gunny bags it Oldonyo Sabuk River.LSK demanded IG Joseph Boinnet provide in 14 days information on the number of extrajudicial killings in the past year.